  "number": 667,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/667",
  "title": "hits: transformData is called on main response when no results",
  "body": "Not sure if this is a bug or a _feature_, but it is in any case suprising.\n\nIf I define a `transformData` method to the `hits` widget, it is correctly called with each hit from the response. But if I do a query that has no results, it is also called, with `data` being equal to the whole API response (including `nbHits`, `hitsPerPage`, `hits`, etc).\n\nThis force me to add a check at the start of my `transformData` to check for `(data.hits && data.hits.length === 0)` (for example) to know that I'm in a \"no results\" call.\n\nThis feels quite hacky, and I think we should provide a better way of handling it. Maybe something like this:\n\n``` javascript\n// pseudo-code...\n\n// transformData only called on each hit, not on the \"no result\" part\nhits({\n  transformData: function() {}\n});\n\n// Passing it as an object lets us define a method for each case\nhits({\n  transformData: {\n    results: function() {},\n    noResults: function() {}\n}\n```\n\nWDYT?\n",
  "created_at": "2015-11-19T11:31:45Z",
